Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of finding lower bounds on the length of a shortest traveling salesman tour in certain classes of graphs. This problem is closely related to topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses techniques from algorithm design and analysis (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC) to prove its results. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
